      "span_text": "This observation seemed to suggest that ethanol had a supportive effect on the hemolytic action of gramicidin S. However, in agreement with earlier studies [CITATION_1] , ethanol turned out to be a crenating agent on its own: minutes after incubation in ethanol only the RBCs transformed to echinocytes (data not shown).",
